1. Product Quality: Assessment of the overall build and material quality.  
2. Battery Life: Duration the camera operates before needing recharge.  
3. User Experience: Overall satisfaction and ease of use reported.  
4. Design Aesthetics: Visual appeal and style of the product.  
5. Compatibility: Suitability with other accessories or devices.  
6. Value for Money: Evaluation of price relative to features offered.  
7. Durability: Ability to withstand wear or damage over time.  
8. Performance in Low Light: Effectiveness in capturing images with minimal light.  
9. Customer Support: Availability and quality of manufacturer assistance.  
10. Portability: Ease of carrying or transporting the camera.  
